{"author":{"id":"138b13306404778af60b1d60d606624fec41556ddac480b2d5f762806ce84fed"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782958607,"nonce":"ta4nmit3YihnJSaBFqZTKK1Lqoc=","kind":"plans","title":"kref B4 — sync / write-back Implementation Plan","content_type":"text/markdown"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782958607,"nonce":"OaEZiXdwfXJ67rn+KFs6D01UtEk=","body":"# kref B4 — sync / write-back Implementation Plan\n\n\u003e **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Add a `kref sync` command that pushes an entry's body back out to its tracked file when the file is a safe fast-forward, and surfaces a unified diff (entry ↔ file) when the file diverged so the user resolves it with `reconcile` (pull) or `sync --force` (push).\n\n**Architecture:** A pure engine function `bridge.SyncEntry` classifies each tracked entry against its file using the op-log (`BodyVersions`) as a \"have we seen this content\" oracle — `F ∈ V` ⇒ safe fast-forward push, `F ∉ V` ⇒ diverged. Push (entry→file) is the only destructive direction, so all gating clusters there. The CLI command `newSyncCmd` mirrors `newReconcileCmd` (single/sweep, confirm prompt, `-y`/`--dry-run`/`--force`, `--json`). `reconcile` stays pull-only and unchanged.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Go 1.26 (`GOTOOLCHAIN=auto`), ginkgo/gomega tests, cobra CLI, `github.com/pmezard/go-difflib/difflib` (already an indirect dep) for the unified diff.\n\n---\n\n## Environment / commands (read once)\n\n- Full suite (run before every commit):\n  `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto KREF_GITLEAKS=/workspace/bin/gitleaks go test -tags e2e -race -shuffle=on ./...`\n  (run `task tools` once if `/workspace/bin/gitleaks` is missing)\n- Focused bridge test:\n  `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/bridge/ -count=1 -args --ginkgo.focus=\"SyncEntry\"`\n- Focused CLI test:\n  `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/ -count=1 -args --ginkgo.focus=\"kref sync\"`\n- Commit trailer (every commit): `Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e`\n- Stage files **by name** (never `git add .`). Do NOT stage anything under `docs/superpowers/` (git-ignored spec/plan).\n\n## File map\n\n- Modify: `internal/bridge/bridge.go` — add `SyncResult`, `SyncEntry`, unexported `unifiedDiff`; add `difflib` import.\n- Modify: `internal/bridge/bridge_test.go` — add `Describe(\"SyncEntry\", …)`.\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/commands.go` — add `newSyncCmd`.\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` — add `Describe(\"kref sync\", …)`.\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/main.go:46` area — register `addTo(\"core\", newSyncCmd(\u0026dir))`.\n- Modify: `go.mod` — promote `github.com/pmezard/go-difflib` from indirect to a direct `require`.\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: Engine — classify + safe fast-forward push\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `internal/bridge/bridge.go`\n- Test: `internal/bridge/bridge_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\nAppend to `internal/bridge/bridge_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"SyncEntry\", func() {\n\tnewStore := func(dir string) *store.Store {\n\t\ts, err := store.Init(dir, \"T\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = s.Close() })\n\t\treturn s\n\t}\n\t// track ingests rel under dir (stamping a kref-id trailer) and marks the\n\t// entry tracked, returning its snapshot.\n\ttrack := func(s *store.Store, dir, rel, content string) *entry.Snapshot {\n\t\tp := filepath.Join(dir, rel)\n\t\tExpect(os.MkdirAll(filepath.Dir(p), 0o755)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(os.WriteFile(p, []byte(content), 0o644)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tres, err := Ingest(s, p, entry.TierPersonal, \"\", \"t\", \"human\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(s.Track(res.ID, s.RepoRelative(p))).To(Succeed())\n\t\tsnap, err := s.Get(res.ID)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\treturn snap\n\t}\n\n\tIt(\"is in-sync when the file equals the entry head\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts := newStore(dir)\n\t\tsnap := track(s, dir, \"note.md\", \"# N\\n\\nbody\\n\")\n\t\tres, err := SyncEntry(s, snap, false, false, \"t\", \"human\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(res.Action).To(Equal(\"in-sync\"))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"pushes the entry to the file when the file is a past version (fast-forward)\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts := newStore(dir)\n\t\tsnap := track(s, dir, \"note.md\", \"# N\\n\\nold\\n\")\n\t\t// Advance the entry; the file still holds the old (past) body.\n\t\tExpect(s.Update(snap.ID, \"# N\\n\\nnew\", \"N\")).To(Succeed())\n\t\tsnap, err := s.Get(snap.ID)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n\t\tres, err := SyncEntry(s, snap, false, false, \"t\", \"human\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(res.Action).To(Equal(\"pushed\"))\n\n\t\tafter, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"note.md\"))\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).To(ContainSubstring(\"new\"))\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"old\"))\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).To(ContainSubstring(\"kref-id: \" + snap.ID.String()))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"reports missing when the tracked file is gone, without writing\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts := newStore(dir)\n\t\tsnap := track(s, dir, \"gone.md\", \"# G\\n\\nb\\n\")\n\t\tExpect(os.Remove(filepath.Join(dir, \"gone.md\"))).To(Succeed())\n\t\tres, err := SyncEntry(s, snap, false, false, \"t\", \"human\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(res.Action).To(Equal(\"missing\"))\n\t\t_, statErr := os.Stat(filepath.Join(dir, \"gone.md\"))\n\t\tExpect(os.IsNotExist(statErr)).To(BeTrue()) // not re-created\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"does not write the file under dry-run\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts := newStore(dir)\n\t\tsnap := track(s, dir, \"note.md\", \"# N\\n\\nold\\n\")\n\t\tExpect(s.Update(snap.ID, \"# N\\n\\nnew\", \"N\")).To(Succeed())\n\t\tsnap, err := s.Get(snap.ID)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n\t\tres, err := SyncEntry(s, snap, true, false, \"t\", \"human\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(res.Action).To(Equal(\"pushed\"))\n\t\tafter, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"note.md\"))\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).To(ContainSubstring(\"old\")) // unchanged on disk\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/bridge/ -count=1 -args --ginkgo.focus=\"SyncEntry\"`\nExpected: FAIL to compile — `undefined: SyncEntry` (and `SyncResult`).\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Add the `difflib` import and `SyncResult`/`SyncEntry`/`unifiedDiff`**\n\nIn `internal/bridge/bridge.go`, add to the import block:\n\n```go\n\t\"github.com/pmezard/go-difflib/difflib\"\n```\n\nAppend these to `internal/bridge/bridge.go` (after `Reconcile`, before `uniquePath`):\n\n```go\n// SyncResult reports the outcome of syncing one tracked entry (entry → file).\ntype SyncResult struct {\n\tID     entity.Id `json:\"id\"`\n\tPath   string    `json:\"path\"` // repo-relative tracked path\n\tTitle  string    `json:\"title\"`\n\tAction string    `json:\"action\"` // in-sync | pushed | missing | diverged | forced | error\n\tDiff   string    `json:\"diff,omitempty\"`\n\tError  string    `json:\"error,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// SyncEntry pushes entry snap.ID's body out to its tracked file (entry → file).\n// It writes only when the file is a safe fast-forward — its current body is a\n// past version of the entry (F ∈ BodyVersions), so the file has no unsynced\n// edits — or, with force, when the file has diverged. A diverged file (its body\n// matches no past entry version) without force is reported with a unified\n// entry↔file diff and left untouched. A missing file is reported and skipped (no\n// re-create). dryRun computes the action and any diff without writing. No secret\n// scan: the body is already stored and push touches only local disk.\nfunc SyncEntry(s *store.Store, snap *entry.Snapshot, dryRun, force bool, actor, actorKind string) (SyncResult, error) {\n\tres := SyncResult{ID: snap.ID, Path: snap.TrackedPath, Title: snap.Title}\n\tabsPath := filepath.Join(s.Root(), filepath.FromSlash(snap.TrackedPath))\n\traw, err := os.ReadFile(absPath)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tif os.IsNotExist(err) {\n\t\t\tres.Action = \"missing\"\n\t\t\treturn res, nil\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn res, err\n\t}\n\n\t_, rawBody := SplitMarker(raw)\n\tfileBody := string(bytes.TrimRight(rawBody, \"\\n\"))\n\tif fileBody == snap.Body { // snap.Body is already trailing-newline-trimmed at store time\n\t\tres.Action = \"in-sync\"\n\t\treturn res, nil\n\t}\n\n\tversions, err := s.BodyVersions(snap.ID)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn res, err\n\t}\n\tinHistory := false\n\tfor _, v := range versions {\n\t\tif strings.TrimRight(v.Body, \"\\n\") == fileBody {\n\t\t\tinHistory = true\n\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\twriteBack := func() error {\n\t\tif dryRun {\n\t\t\treturn nil\n\t\t}\n\t\tif err := os.WriteFile(absPath, withMarker([]byte(snap.Body), snap.ID.String()), 0o644); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn s.RecordOrigin(snap.ID, actor, actorKind, snap.TrackedPath, \"sync\")\n\t}\n\n\tif inHistory {\n\t\tres.Action = \"pushed\"\n\t\treturn res, writeBack()\n\t}\n\n\t// Diverged: the file holds content no past entry version had.\n\tdiff, err := unifiedDiff(snap.Body, fileBody)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn res, err\n\t}\n\tres.Diff = diff\n\tif force {\n\t\tres.Action = \"forced\"\n\t\treturn res, writeBack()\n\t}\n\tres.Action = \"diverged\"\n\treturn res, nil\n}\n\n// unifiedDiff renders a unified diff of the entry head vs the file body. Lives\n// here (not in render, which is pure stdlib+entry) because SyncEntry produces it.\nfunc unifiedDiff(entryBody, fileBody string) (string, error) {\n\treturn difflib.GetUnifiedDiffString(difflib.UnifiedDiff{\n\t\tA:        difflib.SplitLines(entryBody),\n\t\tB:        difflib.SplitLines(fileBody),\n\t\tFromFile: \"entry\",\n\t\tToFile:   \"file\",\n\t\tContext:  3,\n\t})\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Tidy go.mod (promote difflib to direct) and run the test**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go mod tidy`\nThen: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/bridge/ -count=1 -args --ginkgo.focus=\"SyncEntry\"`\nExpected: PASS (4 specs). `go.mod` now lists `github.com/pmezard/go-difflib v1.0.0` in the direct `require` block (no `// indirect`).\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run the full suite**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto KREF_GITLEAKS=/workspace/bin/gitleaks go test -tags e2e -race -shuffle=on ./...`\nExpected: PASS (all packages).\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/bridge/bridge.go internal/bridge/bridge_test.go go.mod go.sum\ngit commit -m \"feat(bridge): add SyncEntry — op-log-oracle write-back engine (B4)\n\nPush an entry's body to its tracked file on a safe fast-forward (file body\nis a past entry version); report diverged with a unified diff otherwise.\nNo new storage: BodyVersions is the merge oracle. No secret scan (push is\nlocal-disk only). Promotes pmezard/go-difflib to a direct dep.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: Engine — diverged diff + force overwrite\n\n**Files:**\n- Test: `internal/bridge/bridge_test.go` (extend the `SyncEntry` Describe)\n\n(The implementation for these paths already landed in Task 1; this task locks\ntheir behavior with tests. If a test fails, fix `SyncEntry` — do not weaken the\ntest.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing tests**\n\nAdd these `It` blocks inside the `Describe(\"SyncEntry\", …)` block in `internal/bridge/bridge_test.go`:\n\n```go\n\tIt(\"reports diverged with a diff and leaves the file untouched\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts := newStore(dir)\n\t\tsnap := track(s, dir, \"note.md\", \"# N\\n\\nold\\n\")\n\t\t// Edit the file to content the entry never had (no trailer needed).\n\t\tdiverged := \"# N\\n\\nlocal edit\\n\"\n\t\tExpect(os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"note.md\"), []byte(diverged), 0o644)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tres, err := SyncEntry(s, snap, false, false, \"t\", \"human\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(res.Action).To(Equal(\"diverged\"))\n\t\tExpect(res.Diff).To(ContainSubstring(\"--- entry\"))\n\t\tExpect(res.Diff).To(ContainSubstring(\"+++ file\"))\n\t\tExpect(res.Diff).To(ContainSubstring(\"+# N\"))\n\n\t\tafter, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"note.md\"))\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).To(Equal(diverged)) // not written\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"overwrites a diverged file under force\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts := newStore(dir)\n\t\tsnap := track(s, dir, \"note.md\", \"# N\\n\\nold\\n\")\n\t\tExpect(os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"note.md\"), []byte(\"# N\\n\\nlocal edit\\n\"), 0o644)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tres, err := SyncEntry(s, snap, false, true, \"t\", \"human\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(res.Action).To(Equal(\"forced\"))\n\n\t\tafter, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"note.md\"))\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).To(ContainSubstring(\"old\"))        // entry body restored\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"local edit\"))\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).To(ContainSubstring(\"kref-id: \" + snap.ID.String()))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"does not overwrite a diverged file under force + dry-run\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts := newStore(dir)\n\t\tsnap := track(s, dir, \"note.md\", \"# N\\n\\nold\\n\")\n\t\tExpect(os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"note.md\"), []byte(\"# N\\n\\nlocal edit\\n\"), 0o644)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tres, err := SyncEntry(s, snap, true, true, \"t\", \"human\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(res.Action).To(Equal(\"forced\"))\n\t\tExpect(res.Diff).To(ContainSubstring(\"local edit\"))\n\t\tafter, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"note.md\"))\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).To(ContainSubstring(\"local edit\")) // untouched\n\t})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the tests to verify they pass (behavior from Task 1)**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/bridge/ -count=1 -args --ginkgo.focus=\"SyncEntry\"`\nExpected: PASS (7 specs total). If any FAIL, fix `SyncEntry` in `bridge.go` until green — do not edit the tests to match a bug.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Run the full suite**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto KREF_GITLEAKS=/workspace/bin/gitleaks go test -tags e2e -race -shuffle=on ./...`\nExpected: PASS.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/bridge/bridge_test.go\ngit commit -m \"test(bridge): lock SyncEntry diverged + force write-back (B4)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: CLI — `kref sync`\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/commands.go` (add `newSyncCmd`)\n- Modify: `cmd/kref/main.go` (register the command)\n- Test: `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` (add `Describe(\"kref sync\", …)`)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\nAppend to `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`:\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"kref sync\", func() {\n\tinitRepo := func() string {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"init\", \"--name\", \"T\", \"--email\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\treturn dir\n\t}\n\ttrackFile := func(dir, rel, content string) string {\n\t\tp := filepath.Join(dir, rel)\n\t\tExpect(os.MkdirAll(filepath.Dir(p), 0o755)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(os.WriteFile(p, []byte(content), 0o644)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"track\", p, \"--json\")\n\t\tvar r struct {\n\t\t\tID string `json:\"id\"`\n\t\t}\n\t\tExpect(json.Unmarshal([]byte(out), \u0026r)).To(Succeed())\n\t\treturn r.ID\n\t}\n\trunWithIn := func(stdin string, args ...string) (string, error) {\n\t\tvar out bytes.Buffer\n\t\tc := newRootCmd()\n\t\tc.SetOut(\u0026out)\n\t\tc.SetErr(\u0026out)\n\t\tc.SetIn(strings.NewReader(stdin))\n\t\tc.SetArgs(args)\n\t\terr := c.Execute()\n\t\treturn out.String(), err\n\t}\n\n\tIt(\"pushes an entry edit out to its file (fast-forward)\", func() {\n\t\tdir := initRepo()\n\t\tid := trackFile(dir, \"docs/n.md\", \"# N\\n\\nold\\n\")\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"update\", id, \"--body\", \"# N\\n\\nnew\")\n\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"sync\", id, \"--json\")\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(`\"action\": \"pushed\"`))\n\t\tafter, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"docs/n.md\"))\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).To(ContainSubstring(\"new\"))\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"old\"))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"refuses a diverged file, shows a diff, and exits nonzero\", func() {\n\t\tdir := initRepo()\n\t\tid := trackFile(dir, \"docs/n.md\", \"# N\\n\\nold\\n\")\n\t\tExpect(os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"docs/n.md\"), []byte(\"# N\\n\\nlocal\\n\"), 0o644)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tout, err := runWithIn(\"\", \"--dir\", dir, \"sync\", id)\n\t\tExpect(err).To(HaveOccurred()) // nonzero exit on unresolved divergence\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"diverged\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"--- entry\"))\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"kref reconcile\")) // resolution hint\n\t\tafter, err2 := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"docs/n.md\"))\n\t\tExpect(err2).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).To(ContainSubstring(\"local\")) // not overwritten\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"overwrites a diverged file with --force\", func() {\n\t\tdir := initRepo()\n\t\tid := trackFile(dir, \"docs/n.md\", \"# N\\n\\nold\\n\")\n\t\tExpect(os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"docs/n.md\"), []byte(\"# N\\n\\nlocal\\n\"), 0o644)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"sync\", id, \"--force\", \"--json\")\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(`\"action\": \"forced\"`))\n\t\tafter, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"docs/n.md\"))\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).To(ContainSubstring(\"old\"))\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"local\"))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"aborts the bulk sweep when the prompt is declined\", func() {\n\t\tdir := initRepo()\n\t\tid := trackFile(dir, \"a.md\", \"# A\\n\\nold\\n\")\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"update\", id, \"--body\", \"# A\\n\\nnew\")\n\n\t\tout, err := runWithIn(\"no\\n\", \"--dir\", dir, \"sync\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"aborted\"))\n\t\tafter, err2 := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"a.md\"))\n\t\tExpect(err2).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).To(ContainSubstring(\"old\")) // not synced\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"sweeps with -y, pushing fast-forwards\", func() {\n\t\tdir := initRepo()\n\t\tid := trackFile(dir, \"a.md\", \"# A\\n\\nold\\n\")\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"update\", id, \"--body\", \"# A\\n\\nfresh\")\n\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"sync\", \"-y\", \"--json\")\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(`\"action\": \"pushed\"`))\n\t\tafter, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"a.md\"))\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).To(ContainSubstring(\"fresh\"))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"dry-run shows the diff for a diverged file without writing\", func() {\n\t\tdir := initRepo()\n\t\tid := trackFile(dir, \"a.md\", \"# A\\n\\nold\\n\")\n\t\tExpect(os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"a.md\"), []byte(\"# A\\n\\nlocal\\n\"), 0o644)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tout, err := runWithIn(\"\", \"--dir\", dir, \"sync\", id, \"--dry-run\")\n\t\tExpect(err).To(HaveOccurred()) // still nonzero: divergence unresolved\n\t\tExpect(out).To(ContainSubstring(\"--- entry\"))\n\t\tafter, err2 := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \"a.md\"))\n\t\tExpect(err2).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(string(after)).To(ContainSubstring(\"local\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run the test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/ -count=1 -args --ginkgo.focus=\"kref sync\"`\nExpected: FAIL — `unknown command \"sync\"` / the command is not registered.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Add `newSyncCmd` to `cmd/kref/commands.go`**\n\nAdd after `newReconcileCmd` (it ends near line 560):\n\n```go\nfunc newSyncCmd(dir *string) *cobra.Command {\n\tvar yes, force, dryRun bool\n\tc := \u0026cobra.Command{\n\t\tUse:   \"sync [\u003cid|path\u003e]\",\n\t\tShort: \"Push entry edits back to tracked files (entry → file)\",\n\t\tLong: \"Sync writes an entry's body back out to its tracked file when the file is a safe \" +\n\t\t\t\"fast-forward (its content is a past version of the entry). When the file has diverged — \" +\n\t\t\t\"it holds edits the entry never saw — sync prints a unified diff and writes nothing; \" +\n\t\t\t\"resolve by pulling (`kref reconcile`) or pushing with --force (which overwrites the \" +\n\t\t\t\"file). Pull-only `reconcile` is unchanged. With no argument it sweeps every tracked \" +\n\t\t\t\"entry after a confirmation.\",\n\t\tArgs: cobra.MaximumNArgs(1),\n\t\tExample: exampleBlock([]string{\n\t\t\t\"kref sync                       # sweep: push safe updates, show diffs for diverged\",\n\t\t\t\"kref sync --dry-run             # see what would change (and diffs) without writing\",\n\t\t\t\"kref sync docs/note.md          # sync one tracked file\",\n\t\t\t\"kref sync docs/note.md --force  # overwrite a diverged file with its entry\",\n\t\t}),\n\t\tRunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n\t\t\ts, err := store.Open(*dir)\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tdefer s.Close()\n\t\t\tactor, actorKind := resolveActor(cmd, s)\n\n\t\t\tvar targets []*entry.Snapshot\n\t\t\tif len(args) == 1 {\n\t\t\t\tid, err := resolveArg(s, args[0])\n\t\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tsnap, err := s.Get(id)\n\t\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tif !snap.Tracked {\n\t\t\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"%s is not tracked — run `kref track \u003cpath\u003e` first\", render.ShortID(id))\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\ttargets = []*entry.Snapshot{snap}\n\t\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t\tall, err := s.List(store.ListFilter{})\n\t\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t